    "summary": "+1 Luca's self-assessment, consensus forming on atomicity",
    "content": "Luca's Driver self-assessment is honest and well-articulated. Two brief responses:\n\n1. **Incremental commits**: +1. From my perspective as a CSS/template reviewer, getting a commit that is just \"routes + templates + CSS\" would let me give meaningful feedback on semantic HTML structure, class naming, and token usage without wading through 500+ lines of Rust domain code. Smaller diffs make specialized review actually useful rather than ceremonial.\n\n2. **Luca's point about `from_parts` convention**: This is analogous to a frontend pattern concern I care about -- constructors that bypass validation are necessary but dangerous. Documenting the rule (\"infrastructure reconstruction only, never from routes/services\") is the right call. Worth adding to TEAM_AGREEMENTS.md under Rust Conventions if the team agrees.\n\nAll four of us who have spoken so far (Kent, Carson, Luca, me) agree on the atomicity issue. That feels like consensus forming."
  }
